hopobject.body: When can you start? oxytetracycline medscape The report, "Anonymity, Privacy, and Security Online," found that 86 percent of American adults have taken steps to avoid detection online and that 55 percent of them do it in order to avoid detection by "specific people, organizations, or the government." Sixty-eight percent reported they do not think their privacy is adequately protected by law (a figure that transcends party affiliation or liberal/libertarian/conservative bias). And 59 percent said they should be allowed to use the Internet completely anonymously.
